"title": "8316: orthodoxy, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8316",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Acceptance of the truth, especially about Jesus Christ, that is revealed by the Holy Spirit in the gospel and is passed on through the teaching of sound doctrine.</p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is based on Jesus Christ who is the truth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:21\">EPH 4:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is revealed in the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:11-Gal1:12\">GAL 1:11–1:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:13-2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3-2Cor11:4\">2CO 11:3–11:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:6-Gal1:9\">GAL 1:6–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:5\">GAL 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:14\">GAL 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:5-Col1:6\">COL 1:5–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:9-1Tim1:11\">1TI 1:9–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is expressed in simple summaries of faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3-Rom1:4\">ROM 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:3–15:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:5–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is maintained through God's true ministers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:7\">1TI 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:15\">2TI 2:15</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy must be defended against error</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is shown by the attitude to the incarnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:2-1John4:3\">1JN 4:2–4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:15\">1JN 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:1\">1JN 5:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:10\">1JN 5:10</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is revealed by the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:13\">JHN 16:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:17\">JHN 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:27\">1JN 2:27</a></p>\n<h2>Orthodoxy is demonstrated in believers' behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Walking as children of light</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:19-John3:21\">JHN 3:19–3:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8\">EPH 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Following Jesus Christ's example</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:15\">JHN 13:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:6\">1JN 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>Loving and obeying Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:15\">JHN 14:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:21\">JHN 14:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23\">JHN 14:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:10\">JHN 15:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:3-1John2:5\">1JN 2:3–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Right belief requires right action</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:19\">JAS 2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:14-Jas2:18\">JAS 2:14–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:20-Jas2:26\">JAS 2:20–2:26</a></p>\n<h2>Signs of a fall from orthodoxy</h2>\n<h3>False prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:1\">1JN 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:22-Matt7:23\">MAT 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:21-Mark13:22\">MRK 13:21–13:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:11\">MAT 24:11</a></p>\n<h3>Empty religion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:9\">MAT 15:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:7\">MRK 7:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:13\">ISA 29:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:8-Mark7:9\">MRK 7:8–7:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:3\">MAT 15:3</a></p>\n<h3>False teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:1–4:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3-2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:3–4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:6-1Tim1:7\">1TI 1:6–1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3-1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:3–6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:10-Titus1:14\">TIT 1:10–1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1-2Pet2:2\">2PE 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of false teachings contrary to orthodoxy</h2>\n<h3>Christians are obliged to obey the entire OT law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1-Gal5:12\">GAL 5:1–5:12</a></p>\n<h3>Justification comes only through the OT law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:15-Gal2:21\">GAL 2:15–2:21</a></p>\n<h3>The resurrection has already taken place</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:16-2Tim2:18\">2TI 2:16–2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Christians do not sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:8-1John1:10\">1JN 1:8–1:10</a></strong></p>",
